[normal]1.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Kirklees Council
[normal] is a 
[normal]metropolitan
[normal] borough
[normal] of 
[normal]West Yorkshire
[normal], Eng
[normal]land. It has a population of approximately 423
[normal],000
[normal], making Kirklees one of the larger local authority districts in England and Wales (ranking eleventh out of 348 districts). Kirklees has approximately 175,000 households, 116,000 (67%) of which are owner occupied. 
[normal]Around 39% of the energy used in Kirklees 
[normal]is for domestic purposes
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Kirklees Council has long been committed to tackling climate change, particularly by reducing domestic carbon emissions. 
[normal]Over the last 10 years the Council has attracted circa £38m of external funding which has provided subsidie
[normal]s for energy improvements to homes. The Council has also contributed 
[normal]c 
[normal]£
[normal]18 million
[normal] 
[normal]capital match funding to deliver energy improvements. 
