[normal]&#xa0;[bold]3.1[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Context / Rationale[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]3.1.1
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]We know that the policies, strategies and services 
[normal]that we develop and deliver
[normal] 
[normal]as a Council 
[normal]have an impact upon the environment and that we have an opportunity to shape a more sustainable fu
[normal]tu
[normal]re to improve people’s lives. 
[normal]The climate is changing, so we must adapt and be prepared for the challenges ahead.
[normal] The Government’s Stern Review in 2006 
[normal]concluded that the benefits of strong, early action on climate change far o
[normal]utweigh the costs of not acti
[normal]ng.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.1.2
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The UK has committed to challenging greenhouse gas reduction targets via the 2008 Climate Change Act
[normal]. As a Local Authority we have a part to play in helping the UK achieve these challenging targets in our role as community leader, service provider
[normal], 
[normal]e
[normal]state manager
[normal] and role model.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.1.3
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]In June 2010 we made a commitment to protect the environment and reduce CO
[normal]2
[normal] as part of the Kirklees Partnership Charter and our Vision commits us to continue to reduce the carbon footprint of Kirklees.
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]3.1.4
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]In 2010, the Council approved 
[normal]its
[normal] [bold]Integrated Investment Strategy (IIS). [bold]This strategy is a framework for investment which sets out the priorities for how the Council will allocate its resources and attract external investment to improve the lives of all Ki
[normal]rklees residents. One of the strategic aims is
[normal] [bold]for a district better prepared to manage the effects of climate change –
[normal] [bold]setting out a clear 40% carbon emissions reduction target by 2020 for both the Council and the District, from a 2005 baseline.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]3.1.5
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal] 
[normal]The 201
[normal]1 Leeds City Region Mini-Stern Review, focussed on the economics of decarbonising the local economy.  A separate appendix was prepared on the Kirklees economy, which identified that: 
[normal]3.1.6
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]In
[normal] response to this, 
[normal]Kirklees Council became an e[bold]a[bold]rly signatory to Climate Local. [bold]Climate Local is a new initiative led by the Local Government Association LGA) to drive, inspire and support council action on climate change. It succ
[normal]eeds the Nottingham Declaration on Climate Change (
[normal]of 
[normal]which Kirklees Council 
[normal]was also a signatory
[normal]) by offering a framework that enables councils to reflect local priorities and opportunities for action. Climate Local focuses on councils’ efforts both to re
[normal]duce carbon emissions and to improve their resilience to the anticipated changes in the climate
[normal].
[normal]3.1.7
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]In December 2012 the Council approved a set of 
[normal]‘
[normal]Climate Local Commitments
[normal]’
[normal] for
[normal] Kirklees to stimulate a green economy and create jobs, 
[normal]help 
[normal]tackle climate chang
[normal]e and provide affordable warmth for our residents, building on achievements to date
[normal]. 
[normal]There are six key headline c
[normal]ommitments 
[normal]as outlined below:
[normal]Creating local jobs in the green sector and ensuring we have the appropriate skill
[normal]s for a low carbon economy
[normal]Continue to aim to provide affordable warmth and tackle fuel poverty. This will help improve the health and wellbeing of Kirklees residents
[normal]Leading by example through the efficient use of energy and water
[normal] in our buildings, street lighting and fuel use by fleet vehicles
[normal]Increasing greener transport and transport connectivity in Kirklees, 
[normal]thus
[normal] 
[normal]reducing 
[normal]transport 
[normal]related carbon emissions.
[normal] Developing future plans to reduce waste and maximise diversion from landfill.
[normal]Deli
[normal]vering a setting for investment, 
[normal]maximising biodiversity and reducing costs.
