[normal]3.2.2[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Working with the public - [bold]Completion of Kirklees Energy Saver Scheme and Kirklees Energy Saver 2[bold] (£400k)[bold]The Council secured £576K from the Government (Department of Energy and Climate Change) 
[normal]as part of a Green Deal pil
[normal]ot initiative 
[normal]to deliver a scheme called Kirklees Energy Saver.
[normal] 
[normal]The
[normal] scheme was launched in January 2013 to home owners and offered free energy assessments and interest free loans or grants via utility - Energy Company Obligation (ECO) - funding. The loans 
[normal]and grants are to install energy saving measures such as boilers, wall insulation, glazing and loft insulation.
[normal] 
[normal]The scheme focused on 10 target areas which were already ‘warmed up’ due to the programme of work 
[normal]previously 
[normal]carried out on Council housing
[normal] in t
[normal]he areas
[normal].  
[normal]The scheme will help over 300 home owners install energy saving measures in their homes via a grant or a loan.
[normal]The 
[normal]Kirklees Energy Saver 2 (KES2)
[normal] project will build on the success of the Kirklees Energy Saver scheme (KES1) which has been
[normal] 
[normal]over-su
[normal]bscribed.
[normal] It 
[normal]will also offer specific support to the most vulnerable residents in Kirklees. There will be an offer of a home visit to provide advice and support and funding for heating r
[normal]epairs and other energy saving
[normal] measures, with
[normal] referrals to partner org
[normal]anisations
[normal].
