[normal]5.3.1[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Collective Energy Switch [bold]Between February and May 2013, 
[normal]Community Energy Direct (CED - a Community Benefit 
[normal]Industrial &amp; Provident Society) conducted a collective energy tariff switch
[normal] as a Department of Energy and Climate Change (DECC)-funded partnership project. Project partners were Kirklees, along with Bradford, Leeds, Wakefield and York local authorities, Ro
[normal]chdale Borough Housing, Fresh Horizons and Wakefield District Housing.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.3.2[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Kirklees Energy Saver[bold]Via a joint bid with Leeds City Council, 
[normal]Kirklees 
[normal]successfully secured £718k 
[normal]from the Department of Energy and Climate Change (DECC) 
[normal]to deliver a 
[normal]green deal 
[normal]pilot
[normal] programme across Kirklees. This will help secure a further circa £425K Energy Company funding (ECO) into Kirklees. The total funding for t
[normal]he pilot is £1.393M which 
[normal]include
[normal]s Council capital of £150k.
[normal] A managing agent and contractor have been procured to de
[normal]liver this project, with close links to an energy supplier.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.3.3[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Leeds City Region Green Deal [bold]Kirklees Council is part of the Leeds City Region collaborative approach to procure a Green Deal and Energy Company Obligation funding and delivery partner
[normal]. Working 
[normal]alongside the ten other Local Authorities in the region, Kirklees is providing valuable input to the scheme which aims to be available for all residents in the city region from April 2014. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]5.3.4[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Climate Local Network[bold]As a Climate Local signatory, Kirklees is r
[normal]epresented at all Climate Local events organised by the Local Government Association and often shares best practice with other Local Authorities. 
