[normal] The UK 
[normal]Climate Change Act 2008
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]sets
[normal] legally binding carbon emission reduction targets for 2020 (reduction of
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]34%
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]in greenhouse gas emissions) and for
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]2050 (reduction of
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]at least 80%
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]in greenhouse gas emissions) from 1990 levels, and introduced five-
[normal]yearly 
[normal]carbon budgets
[normal] to help ensure those targets are met.  In 
[normal]June 
[normal]2011 the Government 
[normal]set in law
[normal] its fourth Carbon Budget to reduce emissions 50% under 1990 levels by 2025.
